title.narrative: OUTPUT 2.1.11: Water, Sanitation, and Hygiene (WASH) IN SCHOOL

description.narrative: Output 2.1.11: By December 2015, government commitment for a National School Sanitation Programme is enhanced based on evidence demonstrated in at least six districts in four provinces., which contributes to Sanitation, Wash In Schools And Ecd Centres, Water. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Programme Component Results (PCR) 2.1 : By 2015, children and women, especially the most vulnerable, benefit from improved access to and delivery of quality basic services such as nutrition, water, sanitation and hygiene, prevention of mother-to-child transmission, health, including in emergencies.
